   0x1110: its odd, because we have three 1'same
 
and we have an IF flag, its basically when we do an interrupt 
    it doesnt actually regard to 80h, its more of like an option of choice 
    so for example 
    if IF = 1, it allows hardware[keyboard, mouse] to interrupt your code
    if IF = 0, it doesnt allow i/o devices to do it

    80h is actually a Software interrupt which happens regardless to IF flag

